{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κρείσσων</b>, ον, <br /> <i>genitive</i> ονος, as always in <i>Epic dialect</i> and old <i>Attic dialect</i>; later <i>Attic dialect</i> <b>κρείττων</b>; <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>κρέσσων</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Fract.” 3, +others, variant in 4th c.BC: Dionysius Tragicus (see. below 11); _Doric dialect_ \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>κάρρων</b> (which see); Cretan dialect <b>κάρτων</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Leg.Gort.” 1.15:\">Refs</a>] — _comparative_ of κρατύς (see. κράτιστος), <b>stronger, mightier</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κ. βασιλεύς, ὅτε χώσεται ἀνδρὶ χέρηϊ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.80 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; especially in battle, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κρείσσοσιν ἶφι μάχεσθαι 21.486; Διὸς κ. νόος ἠέ περ ἀνδρῶν 16.688; κεραυνοῦ κρέσσον.. βέλος 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 8(7).36, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.172, Hp.[same place], etc.; κρείσσων χεῖρας 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 4.4.7; τὸ τοῦ κ. συμφέρον Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Respublica” 338c, compare 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 267 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]: hence, <b>having the upper hand, superior</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ὁππότερος δέ κε νικήσῃ κ. τε γένηται 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.71; κ. ἀρετῇ τε βίῃ τε 23.578 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: as Law-term, of witnesses, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κάρτονανς ἦμεν _prevail,_ Leges Gortynensium \">Refs</a>] [prev. cited] <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> frequently as <i>comparative</i> of ἀγαθός, <b>better</b>, κρέσσονες one's <b>betters</b>, especially in point of rank, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 10(11).39, “N.” 10.72 (but also, _the stronger, more powerful_, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Or.” 710, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.8, etc.); ἐς τοὺς τοκέας καὶ ἐς τοὺς κρέσσονας τεθυμῶσθαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.52, compare “SIG” 685.134 (5th c.BC: Magnes Comicus Mae., 2nd c.BC); οἱ κ. corps of guards at Thebes, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.598e; κρείσσονες θεοί\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], of the <b>greater</b> gods, as opposed to to Oceanus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Pr.” 902 (Lyric poetry); ὁ κ. Ζεύς [prev\\. author] “Ag.” 60 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (<i>anapaest meter</i>); οἱ κ. the <b>Higher Powers</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] “fragment” 10, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sph.” 216b, “Euthd.” 291a, etc.; τὰ κρείσσω, ={τὰ θεῖα}, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 973; τὸ κ.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] the <b>Almighty, Providence,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Corp.Herm. 18.11, 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Ep.” 204, 6th c.AD: Agathias Historicus et Epigrammaticus 1.16, 5th-6th c.AD: Procopius Gazaeus Rhetor “Pan.” p.492; τὰ κρείσσονα\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>] one's <b>advantages</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τὰ ὑπάρχοντα ἡμῖν κρείσσω καταπροδοῦναι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with <i>infinitive</i>, οὔ τις ἐμεῖο κρείσσων.. δόμεναι no one has <b>a better right</b> to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.345; οὐκ ἄλλος κ. παραμυθεῖσθαι Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Politicus” 268b \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κρεῖσσόν ἐστι with <i>infinitive</i>, 'tis <b>better</b> to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κ. γάρ ἐστιν εἰσάπαξ θανεῖν ἢ.. πάσχειν κακῶς Aeschylus Tragicus [{4-5th c.BC}] “Prometheus Vinctus” 750, compare 624, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.52, etc.; τὸ μὴ εἶναι κ. ἢ τὸ ζῆν κακῶς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “fragment” 488, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Apollodorus Comicus 6; also κρείσσων εἰμί\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] with <i>participle</i>, κ. γὰρ ἦσθα μηκέτ᾽ ὢν ἢ ζῶν τυφλός thou wert <b>better</b> not alive, than living blind, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “OT” 1368, compare “Aj.” 635 (Lyric poetry); κ. ἦν ὁ ἀγὼν μὴ γεγενημένος 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.192, compare 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.9. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>genitive</i> or ἤ, <b>too great for, surpassing, beyond</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ὕψος κ. ἐκπηδήματος Aeschylus Tragicus [{4-5th c.BC}] “Agamemnon” 1376 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of evil deeds, κρείσσον᾽ ἀγχόνης <b>too bad</b> for hanging, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “OT” 1374; κρεῖσσον δεργμάτων\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>too bad</b> to look on, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hipp.” 1217; θαυμάτων [prev\\. author] “Ba.” 667 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λέγετι σιγῆς κρεῖσσον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(κρέσσον “PSI” 9.1093) ἢ σιγὴν ἔχε 4th c.BC: Dionysius Tragicus 6; κρείσσον᾽ ἢ λέξαι λόγῳ τολμήματα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 844 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἢ λόγοισιν (i.e. εἰπεῖν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] “IT” 837; ἀναρχία κ. πυρός [prev\\. author] “Hec.” 608 \">Refs</a>]; πρᾶγμα ἐλπίδος κ. γεγενημένον <b>worse</b> than one expected, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.64; κ. λόγου τὸ κάλλος Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Memorabilia” 3.11.1; κ. τῆς ἡμετέρας δυνάμεως [prev\\. author] “Cyr.” 7.5.9 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>having control over, master of</b>, especially of desires and passions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τῶν ἡδονῶν 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 214; τοῦ ἔρωτος Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.1.34 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; γαστρὸς καὶ κερδέων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 4.2.45; αὑτῶν\">Refs</a>] <b>over</b> themselves, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phdr.” 232a, +others; κ. χρημάτων\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>superior to</b> the influence of money, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.60, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.19; τῶν συμμάχων κ. Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Respublica Atheniensium” 2.1 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>putting oneself above</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κ. τοῦ δικαίου 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.84 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κρείσσους ὄντες.. τῷ λογισμῷ ἐς τὸ ἀνέλπιστον τοῦ βεβαίου having reasoned themselves into an absolute belief of the hopelessness of certainty, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 83; φαύλους καὶ κρείττους τῆς παιδείας, ={οὓς παιδευθῆναι ἀδύνατον} (just below), 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Pol.” 1316a9. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>better, more excellent</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἁρμονίη ἀφανὴς φανερῆς κ. 1st c.AD: Heraclitus 54; κ. ἐπ᾽ ἀρετήν 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 181 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ὁ κρείττων λόγος (opposed to ὁ ἥσσων) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nu.” 113; κατὰ τὸ κ.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] in a <b>higher</b> sense, opposed to κατὰ τὸ χεῖρον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Damascius Philosophus “Pr.” 7. \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κρεισσόνως 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 4.4.6, 4th c.AD: Iamblichus Philosophus “Myst.” 7.4; also κρεῖσσον 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 176 (Lyric poetry), “OGI” 90.31 (Rosetta, 2nd c.BC). (κρέσσων from κρέτ-yων, compare κρέτο; κάρτων and κάρρων from κάρτ-yων, compare κάρτο; κρείσσων (like μείζων)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] probably took ει from ὀλείζων.)","strongNumber":"G2908","accentedUnicode":"κρείσσων","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2904","matchingForm":"κράτος","stepTransliteration":"kratos","gloss":"power","_zh_tw_Gloss":"權能","_es_Gloss":"poder","_zh_Gloss":"权能"},{"strongNumber":"G2908","matchingForm":"κρείσσων","stepTransliteration":"kreissōn","gloss":"greater","_zh_tw_Gloss":"更好","_es_Gloss":"mejor","_zh_Gloss":"更好"}],"shortDef":"better, superior, greater","mediumDef":"better, superior, greater <br />can also be spelled <greek>κρεισσων</greek>, <b>better, more useful</b> or <b>profitable, more conducive to good,</b> <ref='1Co.7.8, 38'>1Cor. 7:8, 38</ref>; <b>superior, more excellent, of a higher nature, more valuable,</b> <ref='Heb.1.4'>Heb. 1:4;</ref> 6:9; 7:7, 19, 22","stepGloss":"greater","stepTransliteration":"kreissōn","count":19,"_es_Definition":"superior","_zh_tw_Definition":"更好 (林前 7:38; 腓 1:23)","_zh_Definition":"更好 (林前 7:38; 腓 1:23)","_step_Type":"word","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"spelled\",\"G2908\",\"greater\",19,\"κρείσσων\"],[\"spelled\",\"G2909\",\"stronger\",0,\"κρείττων\"]]","_vi_Definition":"tốt hơn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"更好","_es_Gloss":"mejor","_zh_Gloss":"更好"}]}